HEADWORD: Pousse-caf
<hw>Pousse"-ca`f⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
fr. <ets>pousser</ets> to push + <ets>caf⟦eacute⟧</ets> coffee.]</ety>
<def>A drink served after coffee at dinner, usually one of several
liqueurs, or cordials, of different specific gravities poured so as to
remain separate in layers; hence, such a drink of cordials served at any
time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poussette</ent>⟦br⟧
